{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Nnju1cr4micbaGqL3Vaurv","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a good understanding of the codebase. Let me summarize what needs to be done:\n\n1. Create a new `hive/` package directory\n2. Move `hive_cli.py` to `hive/cli.py`\n3. Move `runner/` under `hive/runner/`\n4. Copy `agents/*.yaml` files as package data under `hive/agents/`\n5. Update `hive_cli.py` (now `hive/cli.py`) to use `importlib.resources` for agent path resolution instead of `os.path.dirname(__file__)`\n6. Do the same for `runner/main.py` (now `hive/runner/main.py`) to resolve agent paths correctly\n7. Update `pyproject.toml` to discover the new `hive` package, remove the old module entry, include the YAML files as package data, and point the entry point to the new location\n8. Update the `Dockerfile` to reference the new module path for the runner\n9. Go through and update all the imports across the codebase to reflect the new structure\n\nNow I need to map out which files to create and move. I'll be creating the new `hive` package structure with `__init__.py` files, moving the CLI code into `hive/cli.py`, and reorganizing the runner module and its submodules (including the VCS adapters) under `hive/runner/`.\n\nI also need to move the agent configuration files into `hive/agents/`. Then I'll update `pyproject.toml` to reflect the new package structure and entry points, and modify the `Dockerfile` accordingly.\n\nThe main code changes involve replacing direct file path operations with `importlib.resources` for better package resource handling, particularly in the CLI and main runner files where they're currently using `os.path.dirname(__file__)` to locate the agents directory.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":11156,"cache_read_input_tokens":29716,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_inpu